Content of communication that takes place on the App
Credit card information for payment
< The information automatically collected when working with external services such
            as X (hereinafter referred to as "External Services")
            >
User ID for External Services
Names and nicknames used in External Services
Profile images used in External Services
Other member information on External Services (friend information, etc.)
< Information automatically obtained on REALITY for Web >
Cookies and other session information
< The information automatically collected from you on the App >
IP address
Device information(Device ID/Device name/Manufacturer/OS, etc.)
Identifier For Vendor
Identifier For Advertisers
For the purpose of studying, analyzing and improving the usage of the App, the Company
            may associate the Identifier For Advertisers with the internal identifier we have given to you.
ⅴ. Purpose of use of the information described in 2 ⅳ
The Company will use the collected information for the following purposes:
Providing the services of the App
Transferring the usage of the App
Communication between users of the App
Display of recommended users within the App
Achieving a secure and safe communication environment
Communication between you and the Company
Studying and analyzing the usage of the App
Conducting marketing research and surveys
Improving the App and fixing bugs
Placement and optimization of advertisements according to your interests and preferences, based on analysis of browsing information, etc.
Rectifying any violations of the Terms of Use
Paying fees with a credit card
Paying Distribution Revenue
Handling inquiries (including identity verification)
Providing information to the third parties set forth in “4. Provision to Third Parties; Information
              Collection Module”
ⅵ. Legal basis
The legal basis for the processing of your personal data is;
Your consent.
Legitimate interests（to improve and enhance user experience on the App by responding inquiries from you etc.）
3. Our Policy regarding Children
The App is not intended for children under 13 years of age, and we do not knowingly collect or solicit
            personal data from anyone under the age of 13 or knowingly allow such persons to use the App. If you are
            under 13, please do not send any information about yourself to us, including your name, address, telephone
            number or e-mail address. No one under the age of 13 may provide any personal data. In the event that we
            learn that we have collected personal data from a child under the age of 13, we will delete that data. If
            you believe that we might have received data from or about a child under the age of 13, please contact us at
            the following "6.Request for Disclosure, Etc.; Inquiries, ⅴ. Controller of your personal data and its
            contacts". As for those who lives in the country or region listed below, we do not process personal data
            from anyone under the following age;
European Economic Area(EEA),United Kingdom: sixteen (16) years old
South Korea: Fourteen (14) years old
4. Provision to Third Parties; Information Collection Module
ⅰ. Provision to third parties
(1) In the cases set forth in "4. Provision to Third Parties" of the “
Basic Policy regarding the Protection of
              Personal Information
,” the Company may disclose personal data to third parties inside and outside the
            country.
(2) When credit card payment is used in the App, the necessary information for payment will be
            provided to Stripe Japan, Inc. and Stripe, Inc. They store and manage credit card information you enter, and
            the Company does not store the credit card information.
(3) When the distribution revenue corresponding to live streaming on the App, is paid by the
            Company through the service of TransferWise Japan K.K., the Company will provide TransferWise
            Japan K.K.. and Wise Payments Limited with the information necessary for the payment of the
            distribution revenue. In addition, upon request from TransferWise Japan K.K., the Company will
            provide TransferWise Japan K.K. and Wise Payments Limited with information regarding your usage of the App.
(4) When using PayPay as a payment method, we will share necessary information to complete the purchase with PayPay Inc. All information you use including your PayPay login information and PayPay user registration information will be solely saved and monitored by PayPay Inc. and will not be saved within our company.
ⅱ. Information collection module
