2025-2-3
“Adfurikun” (“the Service”) is an ad-sorting service provided and operated by GREE X, inc. (“the Company”). This Privacy Policy for End Users Outside of Japan ("the Policy") stipulates collected information from the end users outside of Japan (“End Users”) who view and browse the media that the Company operates outside of Japan (“the Media”) using the Service and the processing of information. This processing of information means any operation or series of operations carried out on personal data or a set of personal data, either by automatic means or otherwise and this operation means acquiring, recording, editing, structuring, storing, modifying or changing, restoring, referring to, using, disclosing by transfer, publicizing or making publicizing possible, aligning or combining, restricting, deleting or destroying.
In receiving User Information (defined below) from End Users, the Company will comply with the laws and regulations regarding the protection of personal information outside of Japan including GDPR, other relevant laws and regulations, and other guidelines, etc., and will use such information appropriately and in light of the Company's business activities.
Please note that End Users residing in the United States should also review the terms and conditions of
Rules and Regulations in Particular Countries.
End Users should review the Policy before viewing or browsing the Media.
1. Acquisition of User Information
Each time an End User displays or clicks on an advertisement on the Media, the End User’s
IDFA
・
Google Advertising ID
, user agent, IP address, device information, and country of residence information ("User Information") will be automatically transmitted to and stored on the servers of the Company and the servers of the Ad Network Operators contracted by the Company.
If the latest and accurate information is not provided to the Company, the End User may not be able to receive appropriate services.
2. Purpose of Use of User Information and Data Retention Period
The Company will use User Information for the following purposes in the Service.
・Confirmation of Advertising Results
・Content Targeting
・Provision of User Information to third parties as described in "5. Provision and Disclosure of User Information”
Personal information will be deleted when it is no longer needed to fulfill the purposes of use described above, except when it is necessary to comply with applicable laws, regulations, or orders of government, courts, and other supervisory authority.
3. Basis for Handling User Information
The Company processes User Information obtained from the End User based on its legitimate interest in displaying the most relevant advertisements to the End User or the End User’s consent to the privacy policy with a link attached to the Policy. In the case of handling by consent, each End User can withdraw its consent at any time. The legality of the handling based on an End User’s consent before withdrawal will not be affected by the withdrawal of consent. End Users who wish to withdraw their consent shall check "8. Suspension of Acquisition of User Information and the Rights of End Users”.
4. Policy on Children
The Service is not intended for children under the age of 16 and the Company will not intentionally collect or request personal data or allow usage of an app by children under the age of 16. If an End User is under the age of 16, please do not send the Company any personal information such as name, address, phone number, email address, etc. Children under the age of 16 may not provide personal information. If personal data of a child under 16 is found to be collected, the Company will delete such data. If the Company seems to have received data from a child under the age of 16, please contact the Company from “10. Contact” below.
5. Provision and Disclosure of User Information
1. Disclosure to Third Parties
The Company may provide and disclose statistic data of User Information sent and stored in the Company’s servers to third parties.
In addition, the Company may disclose User Information to third parties in the cases set forth in "Provision and Disclosure of User Information" in "
PRIVACY POLICY
".
2. Information Collection Module
The Service includes information collection modules provided by third parties that manage and provide ad networks linked to the Service (“Ad Network Operator”). The Company will provide User Information to Ad Network Operators for the purpose of Content Targeting and ad results confirmation, and Ad Network Operators will process the User Information collected by the information collection module in accordance with their own privacy policies. Please check
here
for the privacy policy of each Ad Network Operator.
6. Information Transfer to Third Parties Outside of Japan
The Company stores User Information by itself in Japan. Additionally, the Company will transfer the User Information to its contracted Ad Network Operators located out of the country or region that the End User resides.
In countries in which third parties are located outside of the country or region that the End Users resides, personal data protection laws may not be adequate and appropriate protection measures at the same level as the country or region that the End User resides may not be available. the End User who provides User Information in order to use the Service is deemed to have agreed to the followings:
1. The Company’s handling of User Information in accordance with the Policy
2. Storing and processing of User Information in facilities outside of Japan (including cloud storage and cloud computing operated by third parties) that the Company can use or in contracted contractors of the Company outside of Japan or Ad Network Operators
7. Management of User Information: Security
1. Management of User Information
The Company has appointed a personal information protection manager who is responsible for implementing policies on matters related to User Information and the management of User Information. The Company also provides training and education opportunities to board members and employees to foster a spirit of compliance in accordance with the Policy and the Company’s information handling practices.
2. Security
The Company will use reasonable, organizational, technical, and administrative measures to protect the User Information under our control.
8. Suspension of Acquisition of User Information and the Rights of End Users
The Company complies with the opt-out mechanism set forth by Google or Apple. End Users can suspend or limit the acquisition of User Information by deactivating (opting out of) the User Information acquisition function either on their iOS or Android device.
End Users can also reset User Information on their iOS or Android device. If you wish to restrict the distribution of advertisements using the User Information in the Service, you can do so by configuring the setting on your device.
