here
For Android users: click
here
The Company does not integrate, correlate, connect, or associate, either directly or indirectly, any information obtained from IDFA prior to the reset or information associated with the reset with any previous IDFA.
End Users have rights to access, correct, delete, limit processing, data portability, and raise an objection to their own User Information that the Company holds (“Data Subject Rights”).
Please contact the Company if you wish to request any of the rights to your own User Information that cannot be achieved through iOS or Android device settings, or if you have any questions about how to set up your device.
You also have the right to lodge a complaint about the handling of your personal information with the supervisory authority having jurisdiction over your place of residence.
9. Publication, Amendment, etc. of the Policy
i. Publication and Amendment
The Policy is posted and publicized in the privacy policy of the Media and in the privacy policy link at the bottom of the official website of the Service.
The Company may change the Policy from time to time, and the Company will notify you of any significant changes to the Policy within the Service or at each posting location. The revised Policy will be applied from the time it is posted on the Service or at each posting location.
ii. How to Obtain Consent
Before viewing or browsing the Media, please read and agree to the Policy. By viewing or browsing the Media (or viewing or browsing the Media after any modification has been made to the Policy), the End User is deemed to have agreed with the Policy.
